# BRIEF
#! Creates a simple cmake project using SystemC

=pod

=head1 NAME

B<sc-cmake template> - Creates a simple cmake project using SystemC

=head1 SYNOPSIS

B<new> sc-cmake I<OPTIONS> {:I<NAME>:} SRCS="I<LIST_OF_FILES> VERS=N.M"

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Creates a basic CMakeLists.txt file needed to build SystemC projects.

=head1 PARAMETERS

=over

=item SRCS

List of plain file names for source files.

=item VERS

Version number #.# (defaults to 0.0)

=back

=head1 REQUIREMENTS

An appropriate version of cmake version 3.11 or better should be installed.

SystemC must have been installed using cmake. This is available from
version 2.3.2 onwards.

SYSTEMC_HOME should be defined to point to the SystemC installation directory.

